<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#FF0000">*If HTML and/or <A HREF="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/ubbcode.html" target=_blank>UBB Code</A> are enabled, this means you can use HTML and/or UBB Code in your message.</FONT>
<br>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002373.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Remf da Troll</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hi all-<P>Here's a tip I picked up recently, of relatively limited use but kinda fun and VERY nice for that one particular spot.<P>Warriors can use "pets"!!  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif">  <BR>The cave entrance to the POF in the Ferrott is guarded by a flock of spectres- one outside on hill, one in entrance, ~2 hall patrol, and maybe 4 hidden back in the left branches of the cave.  They ALL seem to be linked tho, so attacking one at lower levels (I'm 44) tended to pull the whole cave out, which is a big mess even with pally / necro / cleric fear kiting.  Makes life as a warrior unfufilling since even careful pulls can end up as a disaster.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/frown.gif"><P>So here's the trick: just north along the west zone wall is a ruin with a couple skeletons or zombies.  Pop an arrow into one of them, but do NOT melee or even face it afterwards (a single riposte will generally kill a skele, tho the zombies tend to be a bit more durable).  Now, with your "pet" following you (and beating on you incessently for 0 or 1 pt of damage!), walk over near the  secret entrance to the cave.  POOF, a spectre or two will warp in and attack- pull it over to the SW zone corner (very close) and put the smack on it w/ yer buddies. Lather- rinse- repeat.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif">  Keep moving farther in the cave as you denude the supply... fairly fast respawn tho, so make sure to watch yer watch.   I've cleaned out the entire cave with a particularly lucky/tough zombie before, one or two specs at a time.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>Why it works: beats me.  I'm GUESSING that having the skele/zombie attacking you increases the aggro radius of the spectres dramatically, and since they attack you instead of you attacking them, an "alert" signal doesn't get sent to the other ones it's linked to.<P>Note: a LOT of people will say "you're aggroing the whole cave", etc.  Simply isn't true.  To get some of the specs to aggro (NEVER attack them directly first), you have to walk almost up to their face, even with a skele beating on you.  If someone doesn't believe you, invite them to come into cave with you and watch you play shadowknight-<BR>in-crafted armor.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>Remf da Troll<BR>44th lvl warrior, karana<P>p.s. anybody else have any fun/useful tips or tricks like this they'd care to share?<P>p.p.s. also, if you ever want a REAL pet, kill the froggie summoners in upper guk, they drop potions of fire ele summoning.  Pretty useless at high level, but fun to play with, and I'd imagine very good for low level twinking as well... (tho not quite in the same league as a dragon tooth  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Way cool and too damned funny.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kupa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thistle Underpants.. err.. .Underbrush in Lessar Faydark has drops a pouch of mistletoe powder, which has one charge of befriend animal... sadly it doesnt seem to actually work =(<P>target a monster, right click on the pouch, it makes a sound like you drinking the potion and gives a senseless message and no pet =(<P>------------------<BR>Kupa FrostHeart<BR>38th Barbarian Warrior<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I think that the idea of attacking a skeleton increasing the aggro radius of the spectres is true.  A number of times I have been attacked out of the blue by a spectre in the feerot just after a wandering skellie aggroed on me.<P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Azreliah Erudite Soulsucker<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.handofevil.org" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B><BR>"we're not an evil guild the name fools you"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've used the same tactic to pull freeport guards. Though it requires some assistance in this particular spot. Basically, I give 1pp to a newbie to lure mobs within guard aggro range. When they run out to kill it, one always seems to stay behind a few seconds longer. If we are unsure about the distance, we pull another mob to the lone guard to get him out more, then tag him.<P>Same trick in CT - using a broodling, you can pull the outter throne room without dumping the whole throne room on ya. Just tag a broodling and bring him up to the steps. Works like a charm.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Keryath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yeah, most clerics have been using the pet skelly trick for ages. <P>Specs have a *huge* assist aggro range, which is why running in there and tagging one will usually get you 4-5 of the suckers. <P>with the little skelly (same faction as specs) just do a fly by of the ent then get a little deeper each time</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
